H0.text: Makes the object move is the effect that gravity always has on an object on Earth.

H1.text: Gravity makes an object stay still on Earth.

H2.text: Pushes the object upward is the effect that gravity always has on an object on Earth.

H3.text: Pulls the object downward is the effect that gravity always has on an object on Earth.

A4.text: The strength of the gravitational field is numerically equal to the acceleration of objects under its influence.

A5.text: The gravitational attraction is directed towards the center of the Earth, which is downward.

A6.text: The Moon's orbital motion is a result of free fall toward the Earth.

A7.text: The velocity of an object in free fall is given by v(t) = v0 - gt, indicating a downward acceleration.
